The scene transitions to an exterior shot of a brick building with arched windows, followed by a cityscape of Sydney, Australia. The woman in the chair, now wearing a black dress with a green and white pattern, claps her hands and smiles. The women on the couch laugh and talk. The woman in the chair speaks to the camera about the importance of intimacy in a relationship. The women on the couch listen attentively. Claire speaks to the camera, expressing her nervousness. The woman in the chair continues speaking, and the women on the couch react with various expressions.

The woman in the chair opens a box and takes out a purple object. The women on the couch react with surprise and laughter. Melissa speaks to the camera, sharing her thoughts on intimacy. The scene changes to Bronte, a 28-year-old online beauty educator from Western Australia, speaking to the camera. She is wearing a gray blazer over a black top. An aerial view of a brick building is shown, followed by an interior shot of three men walking into a room. They sit down on a couch, and the woman in the chair greets them.

Harrison, a 32-year-old builder from New South Wales, speaks to the camera. The men on the couch listen to the woman in the chair. Jesse, a 30-year-old marriage celebrant from Western Australia, speaks to the camera. The woman in the chair continues talking to the men, and they react with various expressions. Josh, a 40-year-old advertising client director from New South Wales, speaks to the camera. The men on the couch listen to the woman in the chair, and some of them laugh. Dan, a 42-year-old digital business owner from Queensland, speaks to the camera. The men on the couch clap their hands, and the woman in the chair smiles.

The video begins with a woman, Tahnee, expressing her excitement about the upcoming retreat. She's looking forward to spending time with the other couples and strengthening their bonds.

Next, we see Harrison, who is struggling with the challenges in his relationship with Bronte. He's feeling frustrated and unsure about the future. He's shown texting Bronte, apologizing for his behavior and expressing his desire to work things out. Bronte replies that she needs space and time to think. Harrison receives a text from Bronte declining his date invitation.

The scene transitions to Ollie, who is excitedly preparing a surprise for Tahnee. He's creating a tropical paradise in their apartment, complete with decorations, snacks, and drinks. He's eager to show Tahnee how much he cares.

The video then shows a montage of couples enjoying their time at the retreat. They're shown participating in various activities, such as paddleboarding, relaxing on the beach, and having romantic dinners.

Ollie surprises Tahnee with his homemade tropical paradise. Tahnee is delighted and touched by his effort. They dress up in Hawaiian attire, enjoy tropical drinks, and take photos together.

Dan and Sandy are shown on their date at a restaurant called Cargo. They have a conversation about their relationship and their hopes for the future. Sandy expresses her concerns about Dan's past relationships and his ability to commit. Dan reassures her that he's serious about their relationship and wants to make it work.

Harrison is shown reflecting on his relationship with Bronte. He's feeling disappointed and unsure about how to move forward. He's shown searching for date ideas online, hoping to plan a special date for Bronte.

The video ends with a scene of Dan and Sandy enjoying their dinner at Cargo. They're shown laughing and having a good time. Sandy expresses her happiness and her hope that their relationship will continue to grow.
